    "text": "The evidence on these points was luite sufficient to justify the use of the strong expressions in the libel, and as the appellant knew the facts, and the jury have ound against him, he must be taken to have known when he e the information that the truth of the libel would be estabThe same argument applies to the question of public fit. If the finding of the jury can be supported as to that, e appellant cannot be heard to say that he might not have ht that the publication was for the public benefit. The were justified in finding as they did on that point.",
