    "original_source_path": "newapp/dataset=decision/decision/commonwealth/1905/decision_commonwealth_1905_9ff1e908.json",
    "text": "One of those defences is at the words are not capable in law of a defamatory meaning, that they were not used in a defamatory sense. Another is at the matter was published on a privileged occasion, which ight be met by proof of malice on the part of the person making the publication. These are defences which the prosecutor must ke into consideration, and should apply his mind to consider ether it was probable that they could be successfully set up, whether the circumstances were such as to deprive the dant of the benefit of the privilege.",
