    "original_source_path": "newapp/dataset=decision/decision/commonwealth/1905/decision_commonwealth_1905_9ff1e908.json",
    "text": "Griffith C.J. HIGH COURT men might in the same case take different views. The jury take one view, but, if reasonable men might take another the plaintiff fails to discharge the onus of proving want of rea able and probable cause.",
    "version_id": "high_court_of_australia:/showbyHandle/1/14123",
