    "original_source_path": "newapp/dataset=decision/decision/commonwealth/1905/decision_commonwealth_1905_9ff1e908.json",
    "text": "O'Connor J. I am of the same opinion. There is no do to the general principle applicable to cases of this kind. is no class of cases in which it is more difficult to explain the' to a jury than those cases in which questions of reasonable probable cause have to be left to them, and the expl becomes more difficult still when the evidence is in con with a prosecution for defamatory libel.",
